place_description: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

reviews_data.review_text: Para pasar una tarde con un cafe y relax

If I could give this location 0 stars I would. I asked for no ice and they left my cup less than half full. I still payed $6. It was gone in under 10 seconds, also to add that my drink mostly consisted of strawberries instead of the actual drink  I came here a few months ago too and they gave me an energy drink instead of my strawberry acai.
Clean, efficient and tasty! A good Starbucks
The staff were very attentive and worked very well together to make dining in a pleasant experience!
I went in for my birthday drink but the app was not working today but the sweet girl at the front (purple hair, and did not get her name) still made me my drink and was so kind about it. Made my day!

I recently stopped by this location for my usual Grande London Fog Latte. I observed a barista (heavy set gal with highlighted hair, didn't get her name) putting 2 pumps of vanilla syrup in my beverage and had to point out that the drink supposed to get four pumps of the syrup. She said that she'd add more syrup however Starbucks had changed their recipes to two pumps and if I wanted more syrup it would be extra next time I order this drink. I thanked her and left. I ordered the same drink from a different location in the next few days and was assured by that store that the drink indeed still gets four pumps of vanilla syrup!
It made me furious that a Starbucks employee would lie to you when being called out for making your beverage wrong! Not the first time I'm having issues with this particular location. I made a special trip and spoke with a manger on duty, she offered me a free beverage which I declined. I'm not sure you can put a price tag on a lie from your employee!? This location has lost my trust and business indefinitely.
Starbucks as always.
Great vibes. The stay was nice and our food was hot and it didn't take to long to get our food and drinks.

One of the barista's whispered about my sister and I to another barista and gave us the "evil eye" the whole time, making us very uncomfortable.  The store manager was not wearing a hat or any head covering which is defiantly violating the dress code, and only one person was wearing their apron. The store itself was clean and organized. But I probably will not go back there.
Good coffee.  Quick.  Not a drive thru location.

This is my go-to Starbucks. It's a few minute drive from my house (and not a bad walk if I'm feeling extra motivated). The employees are always nice, and, unless they are super busy, they get people's orders prepared quickly.

It has indoor seating (and I'd imagine places to charge laptops and other devices, although I'm not certain.) It also has a nice outdoor courtyard area to sit and sip when the weather is nice.

My favorite drinks: cinnamon dolce latte (hot), white chocolate mocha (hot), and the white chocolate mocha frappe. 

The seasonal drinks are also fun, like the pumpkin spice latte, but I usually don't buy them right when they are released. I like to wait until closer to the season/colder weather (for example) because it feels more festive. And I don't get tired of the drink by the time fall gets here.

Favorite food items: chocolate croissant, bacon egg and cheese croissant, spinach and egg white wrap with the guacamole dip (sold separately).

Friendliest Starbucks I've ever been too!

Also the coffee here is different. Tastes like it is brewed right and not burnt.

Will be back for more!
I love this starbucks for multiple reasons. The staff is so kind and warm to talk to, always remembering my orders and my name. And the atmosphere never fails to be great! Definitely recommend!
Good coffee. Always friendly service.
Had a bagel with cream cheese, and cookie crumble mocha frappe. Was very good. Ate in my car, because of being sick.

Noah is fantastic! I am not a huge coffee drinker and was struggling to find a menu item that deviates from my norm. I was wanting to try something new and went over quite a few questions about 3-4 drinks. He offered the option of trying his favorite, which is quite possibly my favorite now, too. Thank you, Noah! Your patience and kindness did not go unnoticed!
Very nice, clean.

The employees here are nice and helpful.  The reason for three stars is because I ordered a venti coffee drink. 6 drinks later and it was gone. I was left with a big cup of ice. I'm not a fast drinker and it almost seemed like a waste of money. The drink was good though!
No one in line , still takes 10 minutes to get a cup of coffee. Customers in the store need to take priority!  Not online orders.
Great courtyard to enjoy.
I really like Starbucks ... the coffee is good, and the atmosphere and furnishings are so conducive for conversation. I had a really nice 2 hours.

I LOVE this Starbucks location for 2 reasons, 1. Convenient location
2. The girls that work there!
Everyday I am greeted by name and they make sure they take great care of me and everyone else! They are so welcoming and always go above and beyond.
Today I am most grateful, because I ordered thru door dash because my morning was cut short-  and inside of the bag was my order, along with the little request I ask of them everytime I go in to get my drink. That made my morning. Truly the best team  10/10
Very efficient, clean, customer service was very courteous, felt important.
Very good.

I wanted to give 5 stars as I really liked this place but today I was so disgusted as when I walked in the two young lady's were engaged on their cell phone as one told me she was showing pictures that she was embarrassed of in 2020. Neither one proceeded to wash their hands after touching the phone. They both touched their hair, then face then one even twisted her nose ring right in front of me again no hand washing. She proceeded to help the other young lady out the lid on my cup touching the rim as well as the lid. I'm in the food industry and this is unacceptable. Management needs to do a better job with training. Phones, noses, hair and face etc carry germs and bacteria.
Best in Charlotte!

Starbucks at Piper Glen is a lovely place to stop any time of day! The courtyard is so appealing to enjoy your coffee! There is lots of comfortable seating to relax or work. Team members were friendly and very efficient! Attentive to food allergies as well! Would love to come here again!

It is a really nice place to sit down and get work done. Staff are really friendly.

BUT I will never understand why Starbucks is that popular. It's below average coffee and it's VERY overpriced. I will say this - if you're a regular, make sure you take advantage of their points program and their partnership with Delta!
Non cordial staff.
Great location, spacious, amazing coffee, great service.

I'm giving 5 stars because of the atmosphere and how the staff handled the crowd, the staff was ONLY 3 people, there were at least 20 of us waiting. I still had a great day overall though

This is my home store, and I always look forward to seeing Wes, Kiera, Kathleen and, more recently, Madison, Nathan and Brianne. My drink is always right; Wes and Kiera often start my order when I walk in the door. Atmosphere is great with regulars like JR and Richard. It is your prototype neighborhood coffee shop. I tutor a student there. Outside patio is also very inviting and comfortable. Great place.
Always and I mean I am ALWAYS at this location. Service is amazing, baristas are rock stars, and they get me order right EVERY TIME

I love this Starbucks it's my favorite.  I go in 3very morning get my coffee and it's like cheers where everyone knows your name. After about a week they caught my name and say hello to me by name and also when they see me coming in they know my drink and alot times by time I pay my drink is ready. Keep it up guys. Yall have turned into my family I live in Tennessee but they make me feel at home while I'm here working. Thanks again.

have fun here with friends

Very bad costumer service bad experience There are no services in this place befitting the size of this big and prestigious name Starbucks, so the taste of coffee and its composition can be found in all its branches except for that location the employee ( Katherine ) who is not good at dealing with the pioneers of this place and her bad style in dealing with customers does not encourage hesitation to this place again !!!

Great service and fun atmosphere. Feels more like local coffee shop than a Starbucks while still having the great quality I expect. I always see a lot of the same people, the baristas are friendly and get to know the customers. It's my new favorite spot!

This location used to be my go-to every morning before work, but the service has gone downhill big time recently, so much so that I completely switched to the much better Piper Glen location. This morning, the app would not let me order ahead at the Piper Glen location, so I decided to give the Stonecrest store another shot. I ordered ahead on the app at 6:56 am, which said 3-6 min pickup time, and did not receive my order (iced coffee and chocolate croissant) until 7:12am almost 20 min later. Meanwhile several people walked in, ordered at the counter, and received their order before I got mine. I asked several people about my order, and all they could say was "it's coming". No apologies, no thanks for my patience, just "its coming". Avoid this location at all costs if you are in any kind of hurry.

30 minutes to get my stupid cup of coffe with low traffic and after me mentioning it to the associates that work there. Then got my coffee to. Dripping all over the place. Got my car filled with coffee same with my clothes. Ruined my weekend, Thank you Starbucks for nothing

The staff  Here was so fast and friendly. They made helpful suggestions.  the interior was nicely decorated for the holidays.. Everything was just as a Starbucks should be. It made us feel like we were back at home. It's too bad we don't live closer cause you would come here often.
Love them....they make my special Pina Colada drink  love atmosphere

Literally never made my drink properly. Warmed up my food when I asked for them to not warm it (I was going to warm it up later and warming it up makes it soggy on my drive)

Kate,Kyrra, and Vincent... the sweetest most polite people ever! I'm from Jersey and I swear they made my entire trip with their hospitality and customer service. Definitely will be back and visit this Starbucks in particular for them !

As I walked in, I suddenly forgot the mask on my face, because the customer service was so on point. Greeted, and helped right away, like a neighbor. Thanks Starbucks, made my day!

I always have a good experience here. The barista at the bar was very personable and chatted with me while I was waiting. Drink was great, and I'm pretty picky. Keep up the great work guys!!!! Baristas rock!!! (From a fellow past sbux barista )

I am an avid fan of Starbucks. But, I don't know why the staff is so weird. There are several instances to quote but I will pen down few of them.

1. Once I placed my mobile order and went with my daughter I kept my bag on the sitting table and started picking up my items. Suddenly the staff started pointing and yelling. I was wondering if I did something wrong. I did tell them I don't intend to eat inside the store and I am leaving. They all stood right there till I was out of the store. I showed them food particles were all over the table. It was clear that a group of people did come before my visit and had spent time. But it was so invisible for them. Weird !!

2. It's been 2 years I have been requesting them not to use ice in my drinks . But I guess this too is non considerable. As per the manager no drink can be made without ice. . I mean really ?

3. I prefer less sweet and that too honey. But these guys are extreme . Either they will make your drink too sweet or no sweet at all.

Overall. Poor staff and poor drinks.
Rude cashier and barista!  First time I've ever made a mental note to not go to a particular Starbucks.
Friendly cashier and not so friendly barista. Will NOT be back.

Absolutely the worst experience.  Combative cashier, who threw her hands up and made a verbal statement of her intent to not take my order before walking away when I attempted to order.  This was done in front of other customers in what can only be stated as an attempt to bully or embarrass me.  The next employee that took my order was very accommodating and engaging. Our customer experience ended with the first cashier coming from the back room and then from behind the counter into my space and loudly demanding to know if we had all we needed and if we found the business cards for her store manager and district manager. Sad

I asked her about the free reusable cup deal and she was very curt, had a bad attitude and was quick to correct me in such a condescending manner. Great customer service I was there on the JOB! Clean as hell yall!!! I loved the whole atmosphere. Yes they have a sign on the door. Wear your mask. And social distant yourselves. Don't be like the Southern Whites like here in Lancaster SC Be SMART like they are in NC! N95 masks....work wear them!

He apologized but then yelled again asking what I got.  Needless to say I told him to figure it out- I already told him and so did his coworker.
20 minutes later... from the time I ordered, I was brought my drink from a nice and responsible older gentleman apologizing for the poor customer service I received.

After picking up my drink I say "thank you", to which I always get no response, or worse, they just keep on gossiping about another customer as if a customer weren't standing right in front of them.  It's very annoying that I choose to spend my money at this store and get rude service.
